.TH "devres_alloc_node" 9 "devres_alloc_node" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devres_alloc_node \- Allocate device resource data
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" devres_alloc_node
.BI "(dr_release_t release "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp "  ","
.BI "int nid "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "release" 12
Release function devres will be associated with
.IP "size" 12
Allocation size
.IP "gfp" 12
Allocation flags
.IP "nid" 12
NUMA node
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate devres of \fIsize\fP bytes.  The allocated area is zeroed, then
associated with \fIrelease\fP.  The returned pointer can be passed to
other devres_*() functions.
.SH "RETURN"
Pointer to allocated devres on success, NULL on failure.
